              <title xml:lang="en">The Lives of the Egyptian Fathers by Palladius, or, as it is here called, "the work of Palladius on the profitable counsels of the holy Fathers."</title>
              <rubric xml:lang="syr">ܥܠ ܚܝܠܗ ܕܐܠܗܐ ܐܒܐ: ܘܥܘܕܪܢܐ ܕܝܚܕܝܐ (sic) ܒܪܐ܇ ܘܣܘܿܝܥܐ
                        ܕܪܘܚܐ ܩܕܝܫܐ܇ ܡ̇ܫܪܝܢܢ ܘܟܬܒܝܢܢ ܡ̣ܟܬܒܢܘܬܐ ܕܦܠܕܝܣ: ܥܠ ܡ̈ܠ̣ܟܐ ܡܘܬܪ̈ܢܐ ܕܣ̈ܒܐ
                        ܩ̈ܕܝܫܐ܇ ܥ̇ܡ̈ܠܝ ܒܐܓܘܢܐ ܕܡܝܬܪܘܬܐ܇ ܘܫ̈ܘܐܠܐ̣ ܘܦܘܿܢܝ ܦܬܓܡ̈ܐ ܕܐܚ̈ܐ ܢܟ̈ܦܐ܇ ܘܪ̈ܚܡ̇ܝ
                        ܡܝܬܪܘܬܐ܀</rubric>
              <note>It is a redaction different from that contained in <bibl type="MS">Add. 12,173<ptr target="https://bl.syriac.uk/ms/69"/>
                </bibl> (see <bibl type="MS">Add. 17,264<ptr target="https://bl.syriac.uk/ms/1080"/>, <citedRange unit="fol">65b</citedRange>
                </bibl>, and <bibl type="MS">Add. 17,263<ptr target="https://bl.syriac.uk/ms/1079"/>
                </bibl>).</note>
              <note>From the description given by <persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/796">Thomas Maragensis</persName> in <bibl>
                  <ref target="https://www.zotero.org/groups/4861694/a_comprehensive_bibliography_on_syriac_studies/items/8RDQK4BB">Assemani's Bibl. Or., t. iii., pars 1</ref>, pp. 145, 146</bibl>, it would appear to be the work of the <persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/474">monk Anan-Yeshua'</persName>.</note>
